---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About — Commonplace" description="About Oli and the thinking behind this personal knowledge garden.">
  <header class="page-header page-shell"><span class="eyebrow">About this place</span><h1 class="display-title">Learning in public,<br />one useful note at a time.</h1></header>
  <section class="section page-shell about-grid"><div class="portrait" aria-hidden="true"><span>O</span><i></i><i></i></div><div class="about-copy"><h2 class="section-title">Hello, I’m Oli.</h2><p class="lede">This is a personal knowledge site for the material I want to understand deeply enough to explain.</p><p>Some ideas become finished posts. Others remain part of a subject space, where lessons can be reorganized and improved as understanding changes. Keeping both formats together makes the site feel less like an archive and more like a working desk.</p><p>The sample content currently demonstrates the architecture. Personal biography, project links, and real social profiles can replace this text without changing the layout.</p><div class="principles"><article><strong>Write plainly</strong><span>Clarity before cleverness.</span></article><article><strong>Connect ideas</strong><span>Context makes facts useful.</span></article><article><strong>Revise openly</strong><span>Notes are allowed to mature.</span></article></div></div></section>
</BaseLayout>
<style>
  .about-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(280px, .7fr) minmax(0, 1.3fr); align-items: start; gap: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 8rem); }.portrait { position: relative; aspect-ratio: 4 / 5; display: grid; place-items: center; overflow: hidden; border-radius: 45% 45% 1rem 1rem; color: #fffaf2; background: #287b7a; box-shadow: var(--shadow-md); }.portrait span { z-index: 2; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 8rem; }.portrait i { position: absolute; width: 230px; height: 230px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.45); border-radius: 50%; }.portrait i:last-child { width: 360px; height: 360px; transform: translate(25%, 30%); }.about-copy > p:not(.lede) { max-width: 720px; color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.8; }.principles { margin-top: 2rem; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: .8rem; }.principles article { padding: 1rem; border-top: 3px solid var(--coral); background: var(--surface); box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm); }.principles strong,.principles span { display:block }.principles strong{font-family:var(--font-serif)}.principles span{margin-top:.25rem;color:var(--muted);font-size:.72rem}@media(max-width:850px){.about-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}.portrait{max-width:420px;width:100%}}@media(max-width:600px){.principles{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
</style>
